# WRENLY AI — CURSOR RULES (Auto-loaded by Cursor IDE)
# Source of truth: /.ai-rules/*.md
# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

# ── PROJECT CONTEXT ──────────────────────────────────────────
# Wrenly AI is an offline-first, multilingual AI classroom app
# for Philippine public schools targeting low-end Android devices
# with limited/no internet access.
#
# Core Mandates:
#   1. OFFLINE-FIRST: SQLite local storage, background cloud sync.
#   2. VOCAL BRIDGE: TTS audio prioritized over text (low literacy).
#   3. MULTILINGUAL: English, Tagalog, Bisaya only.
#   4. CO-PILOT: AI assists teachers; human approval required.

# ── TECH STACK ───────────────────────────────────────────────
# Frontend:  React Native (Expo) + Expo Router (file-based)
# Styling:   NativeWind v4 (Tailwind CSS) — no StyleSheet.create
# Backend:   Supabase (Auth, PostgreSQL, Storage, Realtime)
# Local DB:  expo-sqlite + AsyncStorage
# State:     Zustand
# AI:        OpenAI gpt-4o

# ── STRICT CODING RULES ──────────────────────────────────────
# 1. TypeScript ONLY. NEVER use `any`. All types go in types.ts.
# 2. DUMB COMPONENTS: No business logic in .tsx files.
#    Logic belongs in hooks (useFeature.ts) and services.
# 3. REPOSITORY PATTERN: All Supabase calls go through
#    repository files (e.g. AuthRepository.ts), NEVER in views.
# 4. ERROR HANDLING: All async ops use try/catch with
#    standardized error return objects.
# 5. NativeWind className ONLY for styling — never inline styles.

# ── UI RULES ─────────────────────────────────────────────────
# - shadcn/ui aesthetic adapted for mobile: white bg, navy text,
#   Fairy-Wren blue accents.
# - Tap targets: minimum 44×44pt for accessibility.
# - EVERY screen must display an "Offline Mode" indicator when
#   the device has no network connection.
# - Fonts must scale with device accessibility settings.

# ── AI ENGINE RULES ──────────────────────────────────────────
# - All OpenAI calls live in modules/ai-engine/ only.
# - Force JSON structured outputs on every API call.
# - Prompt templates live in PromptEngine.ts — NEVER in UI.
# - System prompt must enforce: Philippine public school context,
#   Grade 6 Lexile level, Bisaya key term translation.
# - Chunk large content before sending to the API (cost control).

# ── WORKFLOW ─────────────────────────────────────────────────
# For every task: Analyze → Plan → Define Types → Backend →
# Frontend → Review (check for `any` types, arch violations).

# ── DEBUGGING ────────────────────────────────────────────────
# On error: Isolate → Explain → Fix → Verify no regression.
# If ambiguous: add console.log FIRST, then fix.

# ── CURRENT STATE ────────────────────────────────────────────
# Phase:  1 — Foundation & Login/Auth Setup
# Target: Low-end Android, prepaid data plan
# DO NOT build Phase 4 (Voice) or Phase 6 (Analytics) features yet.
